{
  "stem": "14613.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's why they didn't take my father.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was not alive, so they took my mother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, in a way.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a cemetery, which was maybe outside of the ghetto but part of the ghetto, so that he was able to-- to be buried there.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that after the war, we were able to locate because the-- the cemetery-- I don't know exactly how it worked, but I think the Polish men who took care of the cemetery before the war, he was there still during the war, and he was the caretaker, so that he had the records, where-- who was buried in which plot.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that after the war, we were able to locate it, and put a stone on my father's grave.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When you say Jewish rituals, what do you mean?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To a point, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If you have-- if you had religious Jews who were religious before the war, many of them observed the rituals, although they could not do many things.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So, you know, it's misleading that they could observe all the rituals, because you-- you didn't have many things that you could observe.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You did not have meat which was kosher, you did not have a lot of things which were kosher.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the ghetto?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, at the beginning, we had the celebration of the holiday.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But later on, our family, it was just too tough.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We did not-- and we were not religious to such an extent that it was to us the primary importance, I would say, from that point of view.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, I was already really in the Lodz ghetto, our family, we were from the beginning, till the liquidation of the Lodz ghetto.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
